caption: Awesome

My boyfriend and I visited D.C over the weekend and we stumbled upon this restaurant. It was our first time trying Ethiopian food... and let me tell you... the food was exquisite 🙌🏼 Our server was very attentive and the environment was so calm! Loved it!

The restaurant indoor space is nicely organized, dim lighting for night time. The food here is excellent. One of the best Ethiopian food in DC, although I would say that DC have many Ethiopian restaurants comparing to other cities. We had the pork, the beef, and the chicken dishes. They were all good; the meat was tender, flavorful, and spicy. I like that the chicken dish also come with a nice egg, that’s also cooked with the meat. The coffee here is also very tasty and rich, not like your average Starbucks. The only thing was the service were slow; waited an hour from ordering until the food is on the table. Other people don’t seem to have this experience but it happened both times I visited. Food is worth the wait but you can find other places in DC with similar quality and quicker service.
Fantastic food! It's become my go-to during COVID. Their beef seg wat and beef tibs are delicious. I also love their lentils and other veggie options. Highly recommend!

This is far and away the best Ethiopian in the DMV. The njera is so fresh, the wots are so flavourful and the lamb tibs alone are a reason to come. Friends and family who have moved away have had me bring it when I visit. On top of the food, the owners are just lovely people. Such an amazing black owned business to support!
Was great food and we had the whole restaurant to ourselves.
Phenomenal. Spectacular food. Some of the best ethiopian I've had. Excellent pandemic accomodations. Quick service. There was nothing not to love.

Excellent food! I have been eating here for several years now. The restaurant is very clean and the owner and employees are very friendly. During the pandemic, I have been ordering through postmates. Each time the food is quality and always perfect! I have never eaten their food and gotten sick like other ethiopian restaurants. ETHIOPIC restaurant thank you, you are appreciated!!

Incredible food! We've dined in and ordered out MANY times (most during the pandemic) and they are always prompt with their deliveries. The food is excellent quality (I'm especially fond of the Shiro). If you have not eaten Ethiopian food before, know the norms ahead of time: you should be prepared to eat with your hands! I believe they will provide silverware, but you'd be selling yourself short.  Would rate this place a 12 out of 5 if Google allowed. Please do yourself a favor and order from here!
The lamb was tender and delicious! Recommended this place to anybody.

My partner and I love ordering from Ethiopic. Our favorite platter to order is the large vegetarian sampler, which is always incredibly satisfying and filling. They have plenty of vegan options, which is lovely and helpful. The staff is incredibly kind. I’ve always enjoyed my experience.

The portions are small for the price but they are good. They've never been the most organized place either, but they make it work. So, I guess I'm saying there are better Ethiopian spots, but I'll keep going back because the food is good, the place is clean, and the people are nice.

This could happen anywhere, but it happened here last night.  I was enjoying my meal (the food is good) when suddenly my phone started blowing up with texts, emails, and phone calls about fraud alerts.  Evidently someone lifted my bag, probably went into the bathroom, and removed all of my credit cards and a little cash from my wallet.  Thankfully, this person left everything else intact and, surprisingly, hung the bag back on my chair on their way out.  The cards were then all run at a nearby CVS, by either a CVS employee or the thief in collusion with a CVS employee.  Ethiopic was not very helpful when informed of the theft.  At the very least, they could have comped me a drink!  Considering how smooth the theft was, I doubt that this was the first time this happened.  I contacted CVS through social media, and they have already touched based with me by phone and escalated the matter to the district management of the store in question, so they have been much more helpful in this matter.
